author: Tanya Li For Daily Mail Australia
title: Iraqi and Syrian Christians rejected for refugee status | Daily Mail Online
text: Australia rejects '80 per cent of Christian refugees' facing genocide in Iraq and Syria while most refugees entering the country are Muslims, charity says Barnabas Fund claims the rejection of 80 per cent of Christian refugee visas Organisation says the majority of 300 visas were granted to Sunni Muslims They asked Immigration Minister Peter Dutton to investigate the allocations Mr Dutton's office said they had accepted more than 4000 from Syria and Iraq Barnabas has raised $1.2 million to fund the expenses of 1048 Christian refugees Published: 05:18 GMT, 10 February 2017 | Updated: 06:44 GMT, 10 February 2017 31 shares
